Profile?language=EN>Donedan Aumni</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.norrathianknights.com/images/rank4.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/3/02 9:59:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is *dmg bonus*</span><hr size=1> Ok, I am post 50, so say I have a weapon thats 19dmg/25delay (sword of pain), and the bonus is....6(guesstimate) will that make the sword a 25/25? Do tell.<br><br><br><br>You are not your khakis<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ucaioirontoe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CaioIrontoe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Threatening Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/3/02 10:24:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is *dmg bonus*</span><hr size=1> Na dmg bonus is added to your hits randomly. Magic dmg is different tho. Take for instance this sk poker we got in akheva last night. It was 24/32 magic dmg: 6. In this case the weapon really is 30/32(pretty nice, not to mention it had some really nice stats to)<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uugle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warmly Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/3/02 10:33:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ugleduklin.tripod.com/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/dscn0011s.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is *dmg bonus*</span><hr size=1> My understanding is that it's like a Proc (with no message), so for instance, in the example above, if the creature doesn't roll a &quot;save&quot; against that kind of attack, then it could be a 30/32 weapon.  <br><br>My question is, does it become a 30/32 weapon, or is it a 24/32 weapon with +6 to damage?  After all, if you were hitting for say 96 with it as a 24/32 weapon, then you would be hitting for 120 with it as a 30/32 weapon.  Or would you be hitting for 102?  Pretty big difference adding +6 to the damage or increasing the base damage by 6. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uurzah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Urzah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/4/02 4:38:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is *dmg bonus*</span><hr size=1> From what I understand by reading some of the other boards, it's like hitting with another weapon in the same attack.  So a 12/30 bonus 6 would be like hitting with a 12/30 and adding the damage of a 6/30 in the same attack.<br><br>Urzah <p><br><img src=http://www.virtual-empires.com/sigs/UrzahTxt.gif><img src=http://www.virtual-empires.com/sigs/42mage.gif><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68942">My Maglo Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/udldragonbreath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dldragonbreath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/4/02 7:13:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is *dmg bonus*</span><hr size=1> Depends on which type of bonus you want. If your talking the damage bonus you get as you level and gain skill then if it is 6 your min damage will be 7 bonus + 1. IF it is bane damage such as on the lsoee then that is a random added to the damage so if normally it is 16 and you get a magic checked bain damage when it goes through and it is 5 to magic checked damage it becomes a 21 damage weapon.<br><br>DLmystic <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/utulluinbardy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TulluinBardy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/4/02 7:51:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.800india.com/computers/tulluin/dolphinboy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is *dmg bonus*</span><hr size=1> DLMystic is right. Your primary hand damage bonus is added to every attack with your primary hand. Your minimum attack will be 7, if your damage bonus is 6. Damage bonus is not applied to your offhand, thus you can hit for 1. <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=39706><img src=http://www.800india.com/computers/tulluin/tulluinsig33333.jpg border=0></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uparticleboy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>particleboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/6/02 6:04:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is *dmg bonus*</span><hr size=1> Just to add to what TulluinBardy said, damage bonus is purely a function of level.<br><br>For one handed weapons it *was* (level-25)/3 (rounded down).<br><br>For two handed weapons it *was* (level-25)/2 (rounded down)<br><br>I say &quot;was&quot; because this was the old system up until a year or so ago.  Then Verant realised what serious players had known for awhile: and thats the 2h weapons suck.  I can't remember the exact outcome but I think 2h weapons with a delay over 40 got an extra bonus and/or 2h just generally got a bonus.<br><br>At that stage damage bonus wasn't listed on the weapon stats so its existence had been inferred (for example, I'd notice that my warrior's actual critical damage was the damage bonus higher than the &quot;X has hit for critical damage!&quot; message; I forget the exact text).  I guess now that it is listed explicitly it wouldn't be too hard to figure out what the new formula is though I don't htink I've seen it posted anywhere.<br><br>And yes, the bonus is added to every primary hand attack that doesn't miss.<br><br>Its important to consider the damage bonus when comparing weapons.  In your offhand you want the best ratio (damage divided by delay).  In your primary hand you want the best damage output which is compared using this formula:<br><br>(2*damage+damage bonus)/delay<br><br>Whatever weapon that has the best bonus by that formula will do the most raw melee damage over time (assuming identical weapon skills).  Obviously magic damage and procs will complicate this issue.<br><br>Oh as a small anecdote, it was the damage bonus which made the old moss covered branch (and the other one) so ridiculously powerful (considering how easy they were to get).  At level 60, the old damage bonus was (60-25)/3 or 11.  Given a 4/11 weapon thats (2*4+11)/11 or 1.72.  Compare that to, say, the Ragebringer (at 15/25 that would've been about the best available pre-Velious) is a mere 1.64.<br><br><br><br>Hagin Netherblade<br>28th level Barbarian Rogue<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showPrevMessage?topicID=1059.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showNextMessage?topicID=1059.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.ichuu.com/AddReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.emailToFriend?topicID=1059.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.threadControl?topicID=1059.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1059.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1059.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub95.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="innoru